#X text 51 28 You can set a relative tempo length for the conversion. This is sort of like a tempo multiplier. By default we consider the BPM value to correspond to a "1/4" note duration \, but you can set other values. For 3/8 it is the same as a dotted quarter note. You can set this via the argument or the second inlet \, and you can use fractions or decimal values. Besides the list support for the left inlet \, you can also have a list for the arguments or right inlet input. If list sizes mismatch \, the same thing that happens with multichannel signals in math objects like [*~] applies \, where the smaller list wraps and repeats until reaching the size of the longer list., f 74;
